@node stat
@chapter stat is short for Statistics

The stat workspace provides functions to perform statistical calculation
and to organize data for statistical analysis.  It is very much a work
in process.

Current Functions are:

@deffn ‚ąá int ‚Üź stat‚ąÜcount vector

Returns a count of the items in the vector.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá amt ‚Üźslope stat‚ąÜlms‚ąÜintercept data

Computes the y intercept of the Least Mean Squares function given
the slope the that line.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá slope ‚Üź stat‚ąÜlms‚ąÜslope data

Computes the slope of a least mean square regression.  In the data
(a level 2 array) data[;1] is the dependent data and data[;2] the
independent.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá corr ‚Üź stat‚ąÜlms‚ąÜcor data

Calculates the coefficient of correlation of the regression by use
of stat‚ąÜlms‚ąÜslope and stat‚ąÜlms‚ąÜintercept.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá high_low ‚Üź stat‚ąÜrange vector

Returns the range of a data set.  The is the highest amount less
the lowest.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá var ‚Üź stat‚ąÜpopVar vector

Returns the population variance.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá sd ‚Üź stat‚ąÜpopSD vector

Returns the population standard deviation.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá mean ‚Üź stat‚ąÜmean vector

Returns the sample mean of a vector.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá var ‚Üź stat‚ąÜsampleVar vector

Returns the sample variance.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá sd ‚Üź stat‚ąÜsampleSD vector

Returns the sample standard deviation.

@end deffn

@deffn ‚ąá median ‚Üź stat‚ąÜmedian vector

Returns the median.

@end deffn

